Not root users are not allowed to bind to port 80 on the host, or any ports < 1024.  I suspect that is your issue.

https://github.com/containers/libpod/blob/master/rootless.md

@giuseppe What do you think about adding a patch to podman to check for NET_BIND_SERVICE when the user specifies a port < 1024 and throwing an error?

@rhatdan 
Thanks for pointing that out, but I don't think that I have a port issue here. I use `podman run -t -i -a STDIN -a STDOUT -a STDERR -p 8080:80/tcp nextcloud:16-apache` which contains `-p 8080:80/tcp` which as far as I know will bind port 80 from the container to port 8080 of the host.
Also, if I try to start with `-p 80:80/tcp`, then the container will not start to begin with.

@giuseppe 
Thousand thanks, that fixed it :-)

Thank you all for your help and quick responses.
